name: Sally's Strawberry Upside Down Cake
author: Sally Deevers
instructions: Mix strawberries and sugar and let stand 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Put mini marshmallows in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan. Make white cake mix following directions on box. Pour over marshmallows. Pour strawberries over cake mix. Sprinkle Jell-O on top. Bake at 350Â° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve upside down with Cool Whip.
